  "diffSummary": "Reconciliation of the account-switcher feature shipped in the multi-account UI merge. The reactive session store (src/lib/session.svelte.ts) keeps one bucket per logged-in account (Map<accountId, AccountData>); adoptAccount adds rail entries from login/QR/restore profiles, and switchAccount/activate swap the reactive view (conversations, threads, contacts, composer target) to the selected account's bucket. RailNav.svelte renders one avatar per account with an active ring + unread badge + an add-account button. The originally-planned list_accounts/set_active_account Rust commands were intentionally not built — account state is frontend-managed from the existing login/restore profiles. This reconciliation adds a non-secret account-switch diagnostic (account ids + conversation count) and captures the live proof.",
